CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1957, pg. A14 reads:"Women's Day Participants - Among those taking part in annual Women's Day program at Trinity AME Church recently were, left to right: Mrs. Marion Bryant, Mrs. Leroy Mason, Mrs. J.G. Harris, Mrs. Robert L. Vann, Mrs. Oretha Hatcher, Mrs. Charles H. Spivey Jr., Mrs. Frances A. Keith and Mrs. Lillian Petett, Mrs. Hatcher, wife of the Rev. E. C. Hatcher, presiding Bishop of the Third Episcopal District of the AME Church, was the principal speaker. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left, seated: Marion Bryant, Mrs. Leroy Mason, Mrs. J. G. Harris, Jessie Vann, Oretha Hatcher, Mrs. Charles H. Spivey Jr., Frances A. Keith, and Lillian Petett, seated in front of choir in Trinity AME Church for Women's Day program
